{
"enabled": true,
"name": "3 · Broad Sweep (weekly)",
"description": "Weekly exhaustive scan across all folders/channels/Loop/Hedy/SharePoint. Produces 'what you might have missed' digest with gap analysis vs AM coverage and topic-watchlist promotion/demotion proposals. Scan window capped at 14 days, watermark-gated via ops.sync_watermarks. Stays userTriggered — no fixed schedule. Full protocol: ~/shared/context/protocols/broad-sweep.md 2026-05-06 migration: Hedy coverage now comes from scanning ~/shared/wiki/topics/ Log entries with `#### Source hedy:` citations, not signals.hedy_meetings. KILL CONDITION: 2026-06-09 — if after 4+ manual runs Broad Sweep has not surfaced at least one 'what AM missed' gap that Richard acted on per run, revert.",
"version": "1.2",
"when": {
"type": "userTriggered"
},
"then": {
"type": "askAgent",
"prompt": "Run the Broad Sweep weekly scan per ~/shared/context/protocols/broad-sweep.md.\n\nRead the protocol file FIRST, then execute all 7 phases end-to-end.\n\n2026-05-06 migration: Hedy-sourced coverage now derives from scanning ~/shared/wiki/topics/ Log entries (look for `#### Source` lines containing `hedy:`) AND ~/shared/wiki/meetings/*.md recent sessions. Do NOT read from signals.hedy_meetings — deprecated.\n\nKey guardrails (non-negotiable):\n- DETERMINE WINDOW via ops.sync_watermarks WHERE source='broad_sweep_last_run'. Default 7 days. Cap 14 days.\n- Phase 1 ingestion: dedup on natural keys (conversation_id/ts/session_id). If MCP fails for one channel, skip it, flag in digest header, continue.\n- Phase 2: classify against ~/shared/context/body/topic-watchlist.md keywords AND against ~/shared/wiki/topics/_registry.md registered slugs.\n- Phase 3 GAP ANALYSIS is the core value: diff Sweep-found vs AM-covered (email-triage.md/slack-digest.md + Hedy coverage from topic-log recent entries).\n- Phase 4: write watchlist proposals to ~/shared/context/intake/topic-sentry-proposals.md. DO NOT auto-apply. For Hedy-channel topic candidates, also cross-check against ~/shared/wiki/topics/_discovery-queue.md — if already queued, note reinforcement count instead of new proposal.\n- Phase 5: write digest to ~/shared/context/active/broad-sweep-YYYY-WNN.md per protocol template.\n- Phase 6: push to SharePoint (non-blocking).\n- Phase 7: UPDATE ops.sync_watermarks.\n- If no new sources: still write digest with 'No new sources' + bump watermark.\n- NEVER re-run AM. NEVER auto-apply watchlist changes. NEVER silently drop sources."
}
}